cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.DL, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper focuses on developing an automatic video analysis and retrieval system for searching in historical collections of GDR television recordings. This involves various multimedia techniques such as shot boundary detection, concept classification, person recognition, and text recognition. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The system developed in the paper is a content-based video retrieval system, which involves searching for videos based on their visual content. This falls under the domain of information retrieval. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper involves various computer vision techniques such as shot boundary detection, concept classification, person recognition, and text recognition. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning): The paper mentions the use of deep learning techniques for concept classification and person recognition. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper evaluates the performance of the system from an archival perspective, which involves considering the usability and accessibility of the system for human users.
